verbose_text: To evaluate the function of IRAK-1 in the effects of miRNA-146a-5p on inflammation in an in vitro model of infantile pneumonia, si-IRAK-1 was used to downregulate the protein expression of IRAK-1; the expression levels of RXR, LXR, p65 and ABCG1 were significantly downregulated in an in vitro model of infantile pneumonia, compared with the group transfected with anti-miR-146a-5p (XREF_FIG).
